<h1><%= chapter %>. HTML utilities</h1>

<p>The HTML module provides utility functions which can be called from the scripts
<ul>
<li><code>HTML.head(<var>args</var>)</code>
<br>Inserts an HTML <code>&lt;HEAD&gt;</code> section, with <var>args</var> as a
dictionary of options. For instance :
<p>
<dl><dd><pre class="verbatim">
print HTML.head({"title":"HTML Inside Python test",
    'style type="text/css"':"TD {color: blue}"})
</pre></dl>
<p>
<li><code>HTML.table(<var>dict,attrs</var>)</code>
<br>Generates the HTML code for a <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> from a dictionary.
The lines are <var>dict</var>'s items,  <var>attrs</var> is a dictionary with
the table attributes, for instance {"border":"2","cellpadding":"3"}
<p>
<dl><dd><pre class="verbatim">
capitals={'France':'Paris','Germany':'Berlin','Spain':'Madrid','Italy':'Rome'}
print HTML.table(capitals,border="1",cellpadding="4")
</pre></dl>
<p>
<li><code>HTML.select(<var>name,options</var>
<b>[,</b><var>selected</var>
<b>[,</b><var>attrs</var>
<b>]]</b>)</code>
<br>Generates the HTML code for a <code>SELECT</code> named <var>name</var> 
from a list of (value,text) 
<var>options</var>. The option for which value==<var>selected</var> is selected.
<var>attrs</var> are used as key="value" attributes of the SELECT tag
<p>For instance, to print a SELECT with the months and with <code>aMonth</code>
selected :
<dl><dd><pre class="verbatim">
import HTML
print HTML.select("theMonth",
    [ (h,h) for h in range(1,13) ],
    selected=aMonth)
</pre></dl>
<p>

</ul>
</body>
